From e62171768642076a903d29bf1a9aef044d6d5f0f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marc-Antoine Boye <marc-antoine.boye@exail.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Jul 2026 16:16:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] [ghe-data-residency] bind the server to loopback and stop
 crashing on token refresh

The server authenticates no caller and /token answers with the live Copilot
bearer, so binding to every interface handed that token to any host on the
network. It now binds to 127.0.0.1 by default; --hostname exposes it
deliberately.

CORS was applied globally, which let any web page the user visits read /token
from loopback. It is now scoped to /usage, the only route the browser-based
usage viewer needs.

The Copilot token refresh ran in an async setInterval callback that rethrew on
failure. That rejection is unhandled and terminates the process under Node's
default policy, so a single transient network error killed the proxy
mid-session. The current token stays valid for another minute and the next
tick retries.
---
 src/lib/token.ts |  5 ++++-
 src/server.ts    |  7 ++++++-
 src/start.ts     | 15 +++++++++++++++
 3 files changed, 25 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/lib/token.ts b/src/lib/token.ts
index da997d9..a005100 100644
--- a/src/lib/token.ts
+++ b/src/lib/token.ts
@@ -37,8 +37,11 @@ export const setupCopilotToken = async () => {
         consola.info("Refreshed Copilot token:", token)
       }
     } catch (error) {
+      // Deliberately not rethrown: this callback is async, so a rejection here
+      // is unhandled and terminates the process under Node's default policy —
+      // one transient network failure would kill the proxy mid-session. The
+      // current token stays valid for another minute and the next tick retries.
       consola.error("Failed to refresh Copilot token:", error)
-      throw error
     }
   }, refreshInterval)
 }
